$interpreted: Puggi: Put me down! I have human rights!
Pang: What human rights? You don't even have hands, happy feet! How will you smile and wave?
Puggi: Then my Funniest Animals rights?
Pang: Don't try to pull cute eyes on me, you stool pigeon!
Hestia: Ahahahaha, you two are so hilarious! What a friendship you both share~
Pang: Are we?
Hestia: Why not settle down at Maple Lake? My days will never get boring again with you two around.
Puggi: Hehe. Thanks to me, you've got a new friend~
Pang: Oh right. When you were nowhere to be found, I also made acquaintance with a gentleman.
Hestia: Is that so?
Hestia: Well there you have it. Maple Lake sure is a charming place eh? C'mon, settle down!
Pang: Depends whether master will take me in or not......
Hestia: Mhm~ Then let's go pay him a visit!
Hestia: That's the master.

Yan-Bo: Thou canst not then be false to any man,
and one man in his time plays many parts......
......Oh dear, recall can't the next part.
Puggi: Miss Hestia, we're looking for a master, not a disaster...
Pang: ......Indeed, not what I was expecting......
Hestia: Are you sure?! Yet, the only one in Maple Lake with such a background is Yan-Bo and no other!
Pang: Hmm...don't judge a book by its cover. Wait here, I'll go test the waters.
Yan-Bo: Youngling, deeds done to incur your wrath, I remember not.
Hestia: You've got it wrong!
Hestia: Yan-Bo. Pang has come a long way to seek you, hoping you'd take him under your wing.
Yan-Bo: For training?
Pang: Master Yan-Bo, I have been left in awe by your skill! I humbly ask you to accept me as your pupil!
Yan-Bo: Hmm...... from the East Alliance is Sir's attire, true is that not?
Yan-Bo: Sir Pang...well well...
Hestia: Yan-Bo, do you know something?
Yan-Bo: Skill have quite some, from young lad I see.
Yan-Bo: Sharpen your senses, fame come your way, you shall see. My teachings, no need for.
Hestia: Yan-Bo, your tongue twisters are baffling......
Puggi: Old man, you put on quite a show! You flicked Pang away just like that!
Pang: Puggi, shut your beak!
Pang: Master, I.....
Yan-Bo: Enough. Some fruits for dinner I just plucked. Heading home for rest I am.

Yan-Bo: ......Men at some time are masters of their fates,
the miserable have no other medicine but hope.
After that what comes? Or again have I mixed it up?
Hestia: Told you so. Ever since a few years past, when Yan-Bo faced off that bully...
Hestia: He completely shut himself out to the world.
Puggi: What bully?
Yan-Bo: Hestia, eyes of hawk and ears of fox I have.
Pang: Master Yan-Bo, I won't give up so easily! I shall move you with my sincerity!
Puggi: Hey! What now?
Pang: We are going to pluck some fruits, so Master may not worry about an empty stomach. Then he will find the time to train me.

Puggi: To be or not to be, but there's no "we"!
Hestia, save me! Please~
Hestia: What an intriguing duo. I hope they decide to stay.
